commit.message:
merge branch 'fix/issue-29'

close #29
bump maildir to 2.2.3
test against Ruby 2.7.1
remove dependency on ActiveSupport's Object#blank?

replace call to Object#blank?

- Predicate if-statement checks for nil and empty string/array directly,
  rather than relying on ActiveSupport's Object#blank? method.
- Could be simplified further using safe navigation in Ruby >= 2.3, but
  this ensures backwards compatibility with Ruby >= 2.0.0.
bump to 2.2.2

explicitly require #blank? from ActiveSupport

- fix failing tests that depended on an implicit require
- ensure Object#blank? is available in the Maildir::Message class.
- close #27

Merge pull request #23 from CodeGnome/refactor_pullrequest_18

- Refactor pull-request #18 and merge in #24.
- Code should be warning-free now, except for `method redefined` warnings from FakeFS gem.

Sort and align Maildir::Message#new.

Visually clean up the instance variables by putting them in alphabetical
order and aligning the assignment operators.
Remove warning for uninitialized @info

Initialize @counter.

- With a hat tip to @copiousfreetime, this refactoring removes the
  warning about an uninitialized variable when Ruby is run with warnings
  enabled.
- Just because @counter isn't nil doesn't mean it's an Integer, so
  retain the explicit cast.

Ensure @serializer is initialized.

Prevent warnings about @serializer being an unitialized variable when
running with warnings enabled.

Define only getter to avoid warning.

Using attr_accessor creates a getter that is then overwritten by
Maildir#serializer. This change ensures that the getter is only defined
once.
Remove trailing whitespace.

Merge pull request #21 from ktheory/fix-unique-name-mutex

UniqueName: extract mutex to a constant

UniqueName: extract mutex to a constant

It was possible for multiple threads instantiating `UniqueName`s to get different Mutexes.
Update gemspec with maintainer information.
Bump patch version.
Update Travis CI to test latest point releases.
Ignore ctags, etags, and Cloud9 files.
Closes #20.

Teardown after each serializer test.

Add teardown method to reset the default serializer after each test in
TestSerializers.  This prevents errors in TestMessage when tests expect the
default serializer to be an instance of Maildir::Serializer::Base.
Init @@serializer class variable with constant.

Define a real constant for the default serializer.

Since some code relies on the default serializer being an instance of
Maildir::Serializer::Base, there should be a frozen constant to refer to,
rather than just a class variable which can be modified at runtime.

Add failing test for SEED=48094.

Fail when Maildir.serializer is not set to the expected value of
Maildir::Serializer::Base.

Merge pull request #17 from CodeGnome/feature/gem-2.2.0

- Bump gem version.
- Drop support for Ruby < 2.0.0
- Update README.
- Add gem_tasks to Rakefile.

Bump gem version.

Increment the minor version to indicate:

  1. Support for Ruby 1.8 and 1.9 has been dropped.
  2. Unit tests have been refactored to support Ruby 2.x and MiniTest
     5.x.

Note that Ruby 1.8.x is unsupported.

- Ruby 1.9.3 was made the minimum version way back in commit
  639fdb40b26fa2419f715bf1b62c3aeb83526ddd.
- Link to the current version of the Travis-CI configuration file as the
  canonical reference to currently-supported Ruby versions.

Add newly-designated project maintainer to README.

See <https://github.com/ktheory/maildir/pull/17#issuecomment-72490172>
for reference.

Update copyright date in README.

Ensure copyright date includes Aaron's contributions from 2010 through
2014.
